product_name: MaybellineSuper Stay Teddy Tint Long Lasting Matte Lip Tint
summary: SummarySuper Stay Teddy Tint from Maybelline lasts for up to 12 hours. No transfer. In 10 buildable shades. Wear it sheer, blurred, bold or even on cheeks.

reviews.headline: Drying but good overall
reviews.comments: Maybelline's Teddy Tint gives that soft, blurred lip look that's super easy to wear that you can go sheer or build it up for more color. Once it sets, it actually stays put really well, even through meals. It does feel a bit sticky at first, and if your lips are dry, it can get a little crumbly after a while. Overall though, it's a great everyday tint if you want something low maintenance and long wearing, just don't skip the lip balm beforehand!

reviews.headline: The only thing I wear now!
reviews.comments: These take awhile to dry down, but once they do, its not going anywhere. I've eaten pizza, salads with oil-based dressing, pastas, etc. It doesn't leave marks on my water bottle and there's no transfer when I smooch on my baby! It didn't last at all in chlorine though. Kneehigh is my perfect shade and i have one for my purse, one for my makeup drawer, and a backup.

reviews.headline: It's Finicky and It Takes Work, and That's Okay
reviews.comments:
First off, I bought this with the intention to use it primarily as a lipstick, and with the understanding that I shouldn't be using all of the product that's glopped on the wand when you first pull it out of the tube. You really wanna put this on in very light layers, likely after scraping the excess off the applicator, and let it dry down before applying a second coat.
As it stands, when I do that, it dries down quite easily. It does definitely still start off quite tacky, but after some time, the tackiness fades, and what I'm left with is a soft matte finish that isn't too drying (for me, anyhow) and really lasts quite a while. It may not stand up entirely to a super greasy meal like a hardcore liquid lipstick will, but it does hold up rather well to water, snacking, and less greasy foods.
Overall, I do actually like this product. It will not be everyone's cup of tea, and the finicky formula will bother some people, but I personally have enjoyed my tube of Knee High so far, and will likely buy another color sometime in the future.

faceoff_positive.comments:
Maybelline Super Stay Teddy Tint is a lightweight, long-lasting lip color that provides a natural, everyday look. It's a great option for those who want a subtle wash of color that stays put all day.

Pros:

Lightweight: The formula is very lightweight and comfortable to wear, feeling almost like you're not wearing anything at all.
Long-lasting: The color stays put for hours without fading or smearing, making it perfect for busy days.
Natural finish: The finish is very natural and subtle, giving your lips a healthy, flushed look.
Hydrating: The formula is hydrating, keeping your lips feeling soft and comfortable throughout the day.
Wide range of shades: The Super Stay Teddy Tint comes in a variety of shades to suit any skin tone.
Cons:

Can be drying: Some users find the formula to be a bit drying, so it's recommended to use a lip balm or primer beforehand.
Limited color payoff: The color payoff is quite subtle, so if you're looking for a bold, opaque look, this product may not be the best choice.
Overall:

Maybelline Super Stay Teddy Tint is a great option for those who want a natural, low-maintenance lip color that stays put all day. It's lightweight, comfortable, and hydrating, making it a perfect choice for everyday wear. If you're looking for a subtle wash of color that won't require frequent reapplication, this is definitely worth considering.

Additional tips:

For a more intense color, apply multiple layers of the tint.
Use a lip balm or primer beforehand to help the tint stay longer and prevent dryness.
Blot your lips with a tissue after applying to remove any excess product.
faceoff_positive.headline: I love it

faceoff_negative.comments: This lip tint has a somewhat mousse-like consistency when applied to the lips. Upon application after I smooshed my lips together, I noticed that the product was collecting in some of the lines in my lips. It didn't look good. I let it sit on my lips for a little while so I could see the color better and in different lighting around the house. After a while, it still felt like it hadn't dried down yet. I wanted to test that out so I kissed the back of my hand and it left a huge lip print on my hand (see pic). This product claims to be "no transfer. Last up to 12 hours." After I did that however, the product did look better blurred out and more like a matte tint. I was a little shocked when I put this color on because my initial thought was that this shade was more of a corally blush shade but it is for sure Barbie pink! Not really my shade. After I took the tint off my lips, there was still this sticky film sensation left on my lips afterwards that I didn't like. The only redeeming quality in my opinion about this tint is to use it as a blush. I think this should be the intended purpose for this product. I started out small with three tiny dots on my cheek and blended it out with my finger. I added three more tiny dots on top of it and blended it out again. I think it turned out really nice. It blended out really easily, the color is buildable and the product didn't get weird or patchy when more was added on top. On the other cheek, I used three bigger dots about the size of the doe-foot applicator tip and blended that out with my fingers. The effect was a brighter color on my cheek but it blended out just the same and didn't get weird. I also tested the transferability of this product by wiping my face with a white tissue and it only had a whisper of color on it. Touching my face, I can hardly feel that it is there and it feels like my skin. I received this product complimentary in exchange for my honest review.
faceoff_negative.headline: Not for lips, only for cheeks
